      • getPosition

        public void getPosition(double[] position,
               boolean[] update)
        This method returns the current position of the robot.
        Parameters:
        position - Empty double array that will contain the x,y and theta values at the indices 0,1 and 2 respectively after the method ends.
        update - A boolean array that indicates whether the x,y and theta values need to be updated. e.g [true,false,true] will only update the x and theta values while y remains the same as before.

      • setPosition

        public void setPosition(double[] position,
               boolean[] update)
        This method updates the odometer to the values input as parameters.
        Parameters:
        position - A double array that contains the new values of x,y and theta at the indices 0,1 and 2 respectively
        update - A boolean array that indicates which values need to be updated, e.g [true,true,false] means that only the x and y values are updated.
